    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-06-06T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-06-06T14:00:00-05:00" n="502"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d502">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">882.7962/104a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hibbard</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-06-06T15:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 6, 1942—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>141. Please transmit the following secret message signed Marshall to Amler.</p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>It has been agreed by the RAF to extend its West Africa patrols to include
                        defense of the coast of Liberia. For this purpose British have been granted
                        by the War Department permission to operate W/T pack set at Roberts Field
                        and at Fisherman Lake naval radio set for purpose of communicating with
                        Naval and Air patrols off shore. Details as to operational control and
                        location will be arranged by you in collaboration with local representative
                        of Royal Air Force.</p>
                </quote>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
